race.description: Roofing Craftsmen Country Boosted Maiden Handicap
race.comment: DEODEE (3) returned to form last start with an eye-catching second over 1206m at Grafton last start, coming from last at one stage. Draws the fence and meets a very plain bunch so this is her chance. RAINSITPOURS (7) should dictate terms and if left alone is the clear threat. Back in trip after failing over 1526m at Lismore last time out. Nicely drawn and gets in well after Farr's claim so give him another chance. MISS GRAYSEA (5) returned a good figure when a close third over 1215m at Coffs Harbour two back. Failed to fire at Grafton since that run but this looks the right race for a return to form. STRATTON (8) hasn't threatened in three runs this prep but a little step up in distance may see some improvement. TRAVELLER (9) did his best work late last start at the end of 1206m at Grafton so this slightly longer trip should suit.
